# Tribus Hub ‚Äî Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router (TypeScript strict)
- Drizzle ORM + PostgreSQL (Neon)
- Auth.js v5 (next-auth)
- Cloudflare R2 for assets
- Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui + Radix UI
- TanStack Query v5 for server state
- Vitest + React Testing Library for unit tests

## Architecture

### Feature modules (`src/features/<domain>/`)
Each feature owns its UI, hooks and local utilities.
- `components/` ‚Äî React components
- `hooks/` ‚Äî TanStack Query hooks (useQuery / useMutation)
- `lib/` ‚Äî pure helpers, search utilities

### API routes (`src/app/api/`)
- One `route.ts` per resource/sub-resource
- Always validate with Zod before touching the DB
- Return `NextResponse.json({ data })` on success
- Use `toApiError()` from `@/lib/errors` for error responses

### DB layer (`src/lib/`)
- `db/schema.ts` ‚Äî all Drizzle table definitions
- `db/client.ts` ‚Äî singleton `db` instance
- `repositories/` ‚Äî query functions (no business logic)

## Coding rules

### General
- TypeScript strict ‚Äî no `any` unless unavoidable (prefer `unknown`)
- Use `type` imports: `import type { Foo } from "..."`
- No default exports except Next.js pages/layouts/routes
- No barrel `index.ts` re-exports unless the module is a public API

### Components
- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed
- Props interfaces over `React.FC<>` ‚Äî use plain function declarations
- `cn()` from `@/lib/utils/cn` for class merging
- `<DialogTitle className="sr-only">` in every Radix Dialog for accessibility

### Data fetching
- Mutations: always invalidate related queries after success
- Optimistic updates only when UX demands it (complex forms ‚Äî skip)
- `staleTime: 0` for data that changes on every render (e.g., milestones after project selection)

### Forms & validation
- Zod schemas live in `src/lib/schemas/<domain>.schemas.ts`
- API routes validate with `.safeParse()`, return 400 on failure
- Never trust client-sent IDs without auth session check

### Errors
- Use typed errors from `@/lib/errors`: `NotFoundError`, `UnauthorizedError`, etc.
- `isAppError()` + `toApiError()` in API route catch blocks

## Testing

### What to test
- Pure utilities in `src/lib/utils/`
- Zod schemas (valid + invalid shapes)
- Error classes and helpers
- Feature-level search/filter functions

### What NOT to test here
- E2E / functional flows (separate repo)
- Next.js routing internals
- Third-party library behaviour

### Conventions
- Files: `tests/unit/**/*.test.ts` or `tests/unit/**/*.test.tsx`
- Use `describe` + `it` blocks (not `test`)
- `makeProject()` / `makeTask()` factory helpers in test files ‚Äî no inline object literals repeated
- Never mock `@/lib/db/client` ‚Äî tests that need DB use integration tests (separate)

## File naming
- Components: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Hooks: `use-kebab-case.ts`
- Schemas: `<domain>.schemas.ts`
- Repository files: `<domain>.repository.ts`

## Imports
- Always use `@/` alias for src-relative imports
- Group order: React ‚Üí Next.js ‚Üí third-party ‚Üí internal (`@/lib` ‚Üí `@/features` ‚Üí `@/components`)

## Do NOT
- Add `console.log` (use `console.warn`/`console.error` sparingly)
- Create new `/pages/` directory routes ‚Äî App Router only
- Commit `.env.local` or any secrets
- Skip Zod validation on API input
- Add Playwright or any E2E tooling to this repo
